scyBorg Triple-Copyleft Licensing Framework
========================================================================

This software is part of the ecoPrimals ecosystem and is licensed under
the scyBorg triple-copyleft framework. scyBorg is the licensing standard
applied to every primal, every spring, every experiment, every tool, and
every derivative work in the ecosystem.

  scyBorg = AGPL-3.0 (code) + ORC (mechanics) + CC-BY-SA 4.0 (creative)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Layer 1: Software — AGPL-3.0-or-later
------------------------------------------------------------------------

All source code, binaries, shaders, build scripts, configuration, tests,
experiments, and tools are licensed under the GNU Affero General Public
License, version 3 or later, as published by the Free Software Foundation.

This means:
  - Any derivative must also be AGPL-3.0-or-later
  - Network use triggers the distribution obligation (AGPL Section 13)
  - SaaS wrappers around ecoPrimals code must release their source

See LICENSE-AGPL3 for the full license text.
See https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html

------------------------------------------------------------------------
Layer 2: System Mechanics — ORC (Open RPG Creative License)
------------------------------------------------------------------------

The ORC License protects the mechanical designs of the ecoPrimals
ecosystem — the systems, rules, and interaction patterns that define
how primals and springs operate. These are Licensed Material under ORC:

  - Primal interaction protocols (capability discovery, IPC patterns,
    delegation chains, TRUE PRIMAL self-knowledge architecture)
  - Spring deployment niches (niche YAML, deploy graphs, capability
    domain registration, Spring-as-Niche deployment standard)
  - Ecosystem topology (primal composition trios, federation patterns,
    service mesh mechanics, provenance chain structures)
  - Constrained evolution methodology (mutation/selection/fitness
    framework applied to AI-assisted code generation)
  - Game mechanics produced by ludoSpring and other springs (rules,
    stat blocks, progression systems, encounter math)

ORC is irrevocable and perpetual. Derivatives must license their own
mechanical innovations back to the community under the same terms.
No entity can revoke or amend the ORC License.

Registered with the U.S. Library of Congress (TX 9-307-067).

